Psyho's VIM config

INSTALLATION:

1. Check out the repo somewhere (ex. git clone --recursive git://github.com/psyho/dotvim.git ~/dotvim)
2. Install dependencies by running install_dependencies.sh
3. Create the symbolic links by running "cd; ~/dotvim/link_configs.py"
4. Open VIM, type :BundleInstall to install plugins.
5. In vim type:

:ruby puts "#{RUBY_VERSION}-p#{RUBY_PATCHLEVEL}"

Install exactly this ruby and using exactly this ruby generate the makefile and install the plugin (in ~/.vim/bundle/Command-T):

rake make
make

6. PROFIT!

Optional:
Add
alias g="gvim --remote-silent"
to the .bashrc file.
